#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.166"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.166:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.166:0.2"
msgid "17. Paṭipadāvagga"
msgstr "17. Practice"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: chaṭṭhapaṭipadāsuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.166:0.3"
msgid "166. Ubhayasutta"
msgstr "166. Both"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.154"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.166:1.1"
msgid "“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, paṭipadā."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are four ways of practice."

msgctxt "an4.166:1.2"
msgid "Katamā catasso?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.166:1.3"
msgid ""
"Dukkhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, dukkhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā "
"dandhābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā."
msgstr ""
"~Painful practice with slow insight, ~painful practice with swift insight, ~"
"pleasant practice with slow insight, and ~pleasant practice with swift "
"insight."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.166:2.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yāyaṃ paṭipadā dukkhā dandhābhiññā, ayaṃ, bhikkhave, "
"paṭipadā ubhayeneva hīnā akkhāyati. Yampāyaṃ paṭipadā dukkhā, imināpāyaṃ "
"hīnā akkhāyati; yampāyaṃ paṭipadā dandhā, imināpāyaṃ hīnā akkhāyati."
msgstr ""
"Of these, the painful practice with slow insight is said to be inferior in "
"both ways: because it’s painful and because it’s slow."

msgctxt "an4.166:2.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭipadā ubhayeneva hīnā akkhāyati."
msgstr "This practice is said to be inferior in both ways."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.166:3.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yāyaṃ paṭipadā dukkhā khippābhiññā, ayaṃ, bhikkhave, "
"paṭipadā dukkhattā hīnā akkhāyati."
msgstr ""
"The painful practice with swift insight is said to be inferior because it’s "
"painful."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.166:4.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yāyaṃ paṭipadā sukhā dandhābhiññā, ayaṃ, bhikkhave, "
"paṭipadā dandhattā hīnā akkhāyati."
msgstr ""
"The pleasant practice with slow insight is said to be inferior because it’s "
"slow."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.166:5.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yāyaṃ paṭipadā sukhā khippābhiññā, ayaṃ, bhikkhave, "
"paṭipadā ubhayeneva paṇītā akkhāyati. Yampāyaṃ paṭipadā sukhā, imināpāyaṃ "
"paṇītā akkhāyati; yampāyaṃ paṭipadā khippā, imināpāyaṃ paṇītā akkhāyati."
msgstr ""
"The pleasant practice with swift insight is said to be superior in both ways:"
" because it’s pleasant, and because it’s swift."

msgctxt "an4.166:5.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭipadā ubhayeneva paṇītā akkhāyati."
msgstr "This practice is said to be superior in both ways."

msgctxt "an4.166:5.3"
msgid "Imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso paṭipadā”ti."
msgstr "These are the four ways of practice.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.166:5.4"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
